South Africa’s Nine-Year Borrowing Costs Increase at Auction of 2020 Bonds

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-06-28T09:12:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/south-africa-s-nine-year-borrowing-costs-increase-at-auction-of-2020-bonds.html
South Africa ’s nine-year borrowing
costs rose at an auction of government debt, according to
central bank data on Bloomberg.  The Pretoria-based  Reserve Bank  sold 1.3 billion rand of
7.25 percent notes maturing in 2020 at an average yield of 8.29
percent, 10 basis points, or 0.1 percentage point, lower than at
the previous auction of the debt on June 1, the central bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
